    "description": {
      "value": "<div><hr /><div>\n\t\t\t\t<p><i>Prerequisites: 4th level, @feat[strike of the giants|BGG|strike of the giants (frost strike)]</i></p>\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>You've manifested the icy might emblematic of frost giants, granting you the following benefits:</p><ul class=\"rd__list rd__list-hang-notitle\"><li class=\"rd__li \"><p class=\"rd__p-list-item\" data-roll-name-ancestor=\"Ability Score Increase.\"><span class=\"bold rd__list-item-name\">Ability Score Increase.</span> Increase your Strength, Constitution, or Wisdom by 1, to a maximum of 20.</p></li><li class=\"rd__li \"><p class=\"rd__p-list-item\" data-roll-name-ancestor=\"Born of Ice\"><span class=\"bold rd__list-item-name\">Born of Ice.</span> You have resistance to cold damage.</p></li><li class=\"rd__li \"><p class=\"rd__p-list-item\" data-roll-name-ancestor=\"Frigid Retaliation\"><span class=\"bold rd__list-item-name\">Frigid Retaliation.</span> Immediately after a creature you can see within 30 feet of you hits you with an attack roll and deals damage, you can use your reaction to retaliate with a conjured blast of ice. The creature must make a Constitution saving throw (DC equals 8 + your proficiency bonus + the modifier of the ability increased by this feat). On a failed save, the creature takes cold damage equal to [[/damage 1d8]] + your proficiency bonus, and its speed is reduced to 0 until the end of its next turn. You can use this reaction a number of times equal to your proficiency bonus, and you regain all expended uses when you finish a long rest.</p></li></ul></div>\n\t\t\t</div></div>",
      "chat": ""
    },
